      Hat Developer Hub 1.6 or earlier, Red Hat Developer Hub does not automatically
      enable the Quicklinks and Starred Items features. You must manually configure
      these features to display them in the global header. 1. You have access to your
      Red Hat Developer Hub configuration files. 2. You have administrative permissions
      to modify ConfigMaps (if using the Operator). 1. Locate your dynamic-plugin
      configuration. * Operator deployment: The configuration is stored in a ConfigMap
      referenced by your Backstage custom resource (CR). * Helm deployment: The configuration
      is in your values.yaml file or separate configuration files. 2. Enable the global
      header plugin. Ensure that the red-hat-developer-hub-backstage-plugin-global-header
      entry exists under the plugins: list and that disabled is set to false. 3. Verify
      that you enabled the global header plugin. Confirm that you listed the red-hat-developer-hub-backstage-plugin-global-header
