      rules for a Scorecard metric, you use annotations in the `catalog-info.yaml`
      file of a component. These annotations merge with and take precedence over the
      global rules defined in your RHDH `app-config.yaml` file. The annotation key
      must be in the format `scorecard.io/{providerId}.thresholds.rules.{thresholdKey}:
      ''{expression}''`. For example, to override the `warning` and `error` rules
      for the `jira.open_issues` metric, you would add annotations to the component''s
      `metadata` section, such as `scorecard.io/jira.open_issues.thresholds.rules.warning:
      ''10-15''` and `scorecard.io/jira.open_issues.thresholds.rules.error: ''>15''`.
      Any rule that is not overridden in the annotation, like the `success` rule in
      this example, will remain unchanged from the global configuration.'
